 <div class="rec"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><b>4. Defend the value line — skew acquisition to high-PLTV, high-retention channels</b><span class="pill amber">protect value</span></div><div style="margin-top:6px">PLTV/FTD has eased to ~<b>£143</b>/wk (value-mix + heat, plus cohort maturation). Weight growth toward the highest value-per-FTD channels — <b>PPC Generic £221, Unattributed £217, Organic Search £210</b> and lift day-2 activation (welcome-offer/CRM) on the lower-retention lines to protect blended value.</div></div>
 <div class="rec"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><b>5. Lean into the highest-retention channels; investigate the laggards</b><span class="pill amber">quality</span></div><div style="margin-top:6px">First-week APD2+ retention is strongest on <b>PPC Generic 59%</b>, Google UAC 58%</b>, Unattributed 57%</b> and weakest on <b>Direct 36%</b>, Meta Paid Social 36%</b>, Affiliate 46%</b>. Dig into why the low-retention channels (bonus-seeking, onboarding friction, offer mismatch) convert so few FTDs into 2+-day actives, and rework the offer/journey there.</div></div>
-<div class="rec"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><b>6. Manage the forecast heatwave</b><span class="pill amber">this week</span></div><div style="margin-top:6px">The heatwave is forecast to cut FTDs <b>~-4.2%</b> this week (~<b>314 fewer</b>). Shift budget to evening/in-play windows, lean on app/retargeting audiences that are less heat-sensitive, avoid front-loading peak-day spend, and expect a rebound as the spell breaks. Value per FTD should hold, so don't over-react on CPA.</div></div>
+<div class="rec"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><b>6. Manage the forecast heatwave</b><span class="pill amber">this week</span></div><div style="margin-top:6px">The heatwave is forecast to cut FTDs <b>~-4.1%</b> this week (~<b>306 fewer</b>). Shift budget to evening/in-play windows, lean on app/retargeting audiences that are less heat-sensitive, avoid front-loading peak-day spend, and expect a rebound as the spell breaks. Value per FTD should hold, so don't over-react on CPA.</div></div>
 <div class="rec"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><b>7. Fix measurement &amp; invest in CRO over higher CPAs</b><span class="pill grey">enable</span></div><div style="margin-top:6px">Given the affiliate economics, <b>CRO is a better use of marginal budget than higher CPAs</b> — it lifts every channel at zero media cost (Amplitude, heatmapping, welcome-offer testing). Fix <b>Affiliate App</b> tagging (it collapses into Affiliate, so we can't size it). Adopt <b>first-click as an analytical lens</b> to value introducer affiliates while keeping last-click for payouts.</div></div>
 <div class="rec"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><b>8. Spend ATL to amplify brand search — and ring-fence a measurement test</b><span class="pill grey">brand / ATL</span></div><div style="margin-top:6px">ATL (£10.13m H1, 83% TV) isn't trackable per placement and returns only <b>~0.21x</b> on 12-month PLTV, so justify it on multi-year brand value — not last-click CPA. <b>Actions:</b> keep TV as the core but tilt the response weeks to <b>10s</b> (~23% cheaper per incremental FTD, £649 vs £844); <b>uncap brand PPC / Organic / Direct during heavy TV weeks</b> (~62% of the modelled halo lands there — don't let bid caps throttle the demand TV creates); consolidate the small-budget long tail (Sponsorship, Online Video, AVOOH, OOH, LED/partnership boards) into <b>2–3 testable properties</b>; and <b>ring-fence ~10–15% for a regional hold-out or national on/off burst</b> — the only way to turn the ATL model from scenario into measured ROI. Full detail on the <b>ATL model</b> tab.</div></div>
 <p class="note">Recommendations are heuristic prompts from the data, not automated decisions — validate against contract terms, seasonality and RG/compliance before acting. LTV:CAC uses the 12-month net PLTV model; recent cohorts revise up as they mature.</p></section><section class="pane" id="pane-s1"><h2 class="sec">This week — week-to-date + forecast</h2>
